<%= content_for(:title) { 'Sources | Maui Bus Routes' } %>
<h3 class="well app-subheader"><span class="hidden-phone">My&nbsp;</span>Sources</h3>

<div class="mb10">
  <p>
    The PDF bus schedule from the county
    <b>(<a href="http://co.maui.hi.us/documents/21/BusFixRouteSchedule_201212281341180673.pdf" target="_blank">co.maui.hi.us</a>)</b>
    was useful as a starting point, but is way out of date. The map images
    <b>(<a href="http://mobilemaplets.com/showplace/8327" target="_blank">mobilemaplets.com</a>)</b>
    were useful for finding stops not listed on the PDF. Google Maps for their API, which I used to create the maps and draw routes. Also for listing bus stops and times not listed by the county.
  </p>
  <ul class="">
    <li><%= link_to('Google Maps', 'https://maps.google.com/', target: '_blank') %></li>
    <% @files.each do |f| %>
        <li><%= link_to(f, "/sources/#{f}") %></li>
    <% end %>
  </ul>
</div>
<%= render('regions/insight') %>